<subSubSection id="AC8E4B8151B318DCFF0EF8EEEB931F8C" lastPageId="138" lastPageNumber="139" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E42B180A51B318DEFF0EF8EEEBA71B93" blockId="136.[151,1437,1905,2005]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B318DEFF0EF8EEEE321BCB" bold="true" box="[151,266,1905,1932]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 12.0 mm long; light brown dorsally with pinkish fat body visible beneath pronotum; most obviously distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951B318DEFE16F809ED2E1BF7" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1939" box="[399,534,1942,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B318DEFE16F809ED2E1BF7" box="[399,534,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Pygoluciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the posterior margin of T8 which is narrowly downturned but does not engulf 
<date id="902A3ECA51B318DEFF0EF824EF811B92" box="[151,185,1979,2005]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V7</date>
apex; otherwise similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2394638951B318DEFE70F824ED671B93" box="[489,607,1979,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qingyu">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B318DEFE70F824ED671B93" box="[489,607,1979,2004]" italics="true" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Py. qingyu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where neither 
<date id="902A3ECA51B318DEFC9FF824EC101B92" box="[774,808,1979,2005]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">V7</date>
nor T8 are noticeably prolonged.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B0EB488251B218DFFF0EF8FBEE921BAE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" startId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" targetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" targetPageId="137">
<paragraph id="E42B180A51B218DFFF0EF8FBEE921BAE" blockId="137.[151,1436,1892,2025]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B218DFFF0EF8FBEE481B3A" bold="true" box="[151,368,1892,1917]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">FIGURES 437−448.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2394638951B218DFFEE0F8FAED701B3A" authority="Ho, 2019" authorityName="Ho" authorityYear="2019" box="[377,584,1893,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygoluciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phupan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B218DFFEE0F8FAED701B3A" box="[377,584,1893,1917]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Pygoluciola phupan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B218DFFDC9F8FAED9B1B3A" bold="true" box="[592,675,1893,1917]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CDD3796351B218DFFDC9F8FAED9B1B3A" box="[592,675,1893,1917]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E42B180A51B118DCFF5EFF06ED611FE0" blockId="138.[151,1437,153,1043]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis id="D6E0C41851B118DCFF5EFF06EE331CF4" bold="true" box="[199,267,153,179]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Male.</emphasis>
12.0 mm long. Colour (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFDB1FF06EDF51CF4" box="[552,717,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Figs 437−444</figureCitation>
): dorsally light brown with white elytral apices (accumulation of fat body) and suture pale in apical 2/3; viewed from beneath elytral apex is narrowly darker brown; pronotum semitransparent with pink fat body visible beneath cuticle in a rectangular shape which is wider than long; venter of thorax, all tibiae and tarsi, and basal abdominal ventrites very dark almost black; remainder of legs pale brown; LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA51B118DCFF2AFEB6EFE01D04" box="[179,216,297,323]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">V6</date>
, 7 creamy white; LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA51B118DCFE7EFEB6ED311D04" box="[487,521,297,323]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">V7</date>
retracted from lateral margins and extending into base of MPP (Fig. shows specimen after soaking in soapy water when and LO material has apparently retracted from the dorsal surface of 
<date id="902A3ECA51B118DCFAF0FED2EAB71D20" box="[1385,1423,333,359]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">V7</date>
); all abdominal tergites except T8 very dark almost black; T8 orange yellow (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFC65FEEEEA2A1DCC" box="[1020,1298,369,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Figs 439, 440, 443, 444</figureCitation>
). Pronotum: lateral margins slightly convex sided (B&gt; A, C); posterolateral corners acute projecting as far as posterior median margin; width less than humeral width. Elytron: very slightly convex sided; no interstitial lines; punctures conspicuous but not enlarged. Head: certain aspects not visible (not possible to remove whitish glue used to stick specimen to card). Antennae: slightly longer than GHW; scape longer than FS; all FS elongate slender at least 3 times as long as wide or longer. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFE7DFDBAEDBE1E78" box="[484,646,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Figs 439−444</figureCitation>
): LO in 
<date id="902A3ECA51B118DCFD7AFDBAEC3D1E78" box="[739,773,549,575]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">V7</date>
parallel sided with a slightly acute posterior margin which just reaches into the apically rounded MPP which inclines slightly dorsally; lateral and posterior margins of dorsal surface of 
<date id="902A3ECA51B118DCFE8BFDF2EE0C1EC0" box="[274,308,621,647]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">V7</date>
dorsally reflexed, not engulfing any abdominal tergites. T8 (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFC6AFDF2EA351EC0" box="[1011,1293,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Figs 439, 440, 442−444</figureCitation>
): subparallel sided, with posterior margin narrowly inclined ventrally but not enveloping the MPP; anterolateral arms of T8 elongate slender, expanded in vertical plane and longer than posterior entire portion of T8; bearing short pointed semimembranous projections on their ventral surface (position indicated on 
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFC6DFD46EB6F1EB4" box="[1012,1111,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Fig. 440</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFAABFD46EFFE1F50" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Figs 447, 448</figureCitation>
): posterior margin of tergite rounded; basal 5/7 of sheath sternite very narrow, expanding in apical 2/7 with lateral sclerotized pieces of sternite apically divergent and bearing paired hairy lobes which project beyond the tergite apex. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="7CAF048F51B118DCFECDFCDAEECA1F27" box="[340,498,836,864]" captionStart="FIGURES 437−448" captionStartId="137.[151,264,1892,1917]" captionTargetBox="[202,1361,166,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@137.[202,1362,166,1873]" captionTargetPageId="137" captionText="FIGURES 437−448. Pygoluciola phupan sp. nov. type males. 437, 438 habitus dorsal; 439, 440 tergite 8: 439 ventral; 440 right lateral (projections arrowed); 441 habitus ventral; 442− 444 abdomen: 442 ventral; 443 dorsal; 444 right lateral; 445, 446 aedeagus: 445 ventral; 446 dorsal (transmitted light); 447, 448 aedeagal sheath: 447 dorsal; 448 ventral. Scale lines are 1 mm unless otherwise indicated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508269/files/figure.png" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Figs 445, 446</figureCitation>
): elongate narrow, slightly wider across base of LL than elsewhere; apical half of LL elongate membranous as wide at base as at apex and extending well beyond rounded apex of ML; dorsal base of LL asymmetrical produced on its right side.
</paragraph>
